[0.113967, "o", "# pm QA library\r\n\r\nEvery project that uses `pm` gets a `pm/qa/` directory with four\r\nsubdirectories of Markdown-with-frontmatter files. They feed prompts,\r\nthe TUI, and the CLI.\r\n\r\n## The four directories\r\n\r\n| Directory | Purpose |\r\n|---|---|\r\n| `pm/qa/instructions/` | Reusable test-environment procedures — anything a QA scenario needs to set up before it can exercise the code (seed a database, start a dev server, prepare fixture data, log in a test user, etc.). Referenced by QA scenarios in their `INSTRUCTION:` field. |\r\n| `pm/qa/regression/`   | Claude-driven test scenarios run via `pm qa regression <id>`. Each file is a natural-language prompt; the runner launches Claude with the prompt to exercise the project end-to-end and report back. |\r\n| `pm/qa/artifacts/`    | Recipes for capturing concrete evidence of behavior — recordings, logs, screenshots — that unambiguously confirm what happened. |\r\n| `pm/qa/mocks/`        | Shared mock definitions injected verbatim into every QA scenario prompt so all sc"]
[0.114012, "o", "enarios use the same contracts for external dependencies. |\r\n\r\nThere is also a runtime sibling, `pm/qa/captures/`, written by impl,\r\nQA, and regression sessions — see [Captures](#captures) below.\r\n\r\n## Authoring\r\n\r\n"]
[0.122908, "o", "+ /tmp/pm-pkg-venv/bin/pm qa docs\r\n"]
[0.122983, "o", "+ wc -l\r\n"]
[0.168404, "o", "342\r\n"]
[0.16872, "o", "+ /tmp/pm-pkg-venv/bin/pm qa docs\r\n"]
[0.218681, "o", "+ echo exit=0\r\nexit=0\r\n+ grep -c '^# pm QA library' /tmp/qa-docs.out\r\n"]
[0.219972, "o", "1\r\n"]
[0.22013, "o", "+ grep -c '^## Instructions' /tmp/qa-docs.out\r\n"]
[0.221103, "o", "1\r\n"]
[0.221166, "o", "+ grep -c '^## Regression tests' /tmp/qa-docs.out\r\n"]
[0.222277, "o", "1\r\n"]
